<h3 id="faq">FAQ</h3>
<h4>What are the requirements for my phone?</h4>
<ul>
  	<li><i>Recommanded</i>: A "data plan" for Internet access to transmit measurement in real time</li>
	<li><i>Recommanded</i>: A GPS receiver, either built-in or external (connected through Bluetooth)</li>
        <li>Platform specifics:
        	<ul>
        		<li>For Android phones: Android OS version 2.1 or later (minimal API level 7).</li>
        		<li>For Java ME phones:
          			<div id="jsr">
                			<ul>
						<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connected_Limited_Device_Configuration">Connected Limited Device Configuration (CLDC)</a>, v1.1 or higher</li>
						<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mobile_Information_Device_Profile">Mobile Information Device Profile (MIDP)</a>, v2.0 or higher</li>
						<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Mobile_Media_API">JSR-135 Mobile Media API (MMAPI)</a>, v1.0 or higher, with support for recording audio in PCM, WAV, AU or RAW format</li>
						<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mobile_Information_Device_Profile#javax.microedition.io.file">JSR-75 FileConnection Optional Package (FCOP)</a>, v1.0 or higher</li>
						<li><i>Optional</i>: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Location_API_for_Java_ME">JSR-179 Location API</a>, v1.0 or higher (for GPS support)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
		        </li>

		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>
